{"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Related Documentation","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI"},{"text":" documentation provides the matching API reference for the modifiers described here.","type":"text"}],"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPresentTheUI"],"anchor":"Related-Documentation"},{"generated":true,"title":"Explanation","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/EntitlementMapping"],"anchor":"Explanation"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The bundled UI is intentionally opinionated. Each modifier picks the platform-appropriate presentation so consumers don’t have to repeat the conditional compilation themselves, and so the dispatch flow stays symmetric across platforms — the same "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".paywall(.dismiss)"},{"type":"text","text":" action fires from a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fullScreenCover"},{"type":"text","text":" on iOS and from a sheet on macOS."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This article explains the reasoning behind those choices and what is fixed versus configurable.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"revenueCatPaywall","anchor":"revenueCatPaywall","type":"heading","level":2},{"header":"row","type":"table","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Platform"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Presentation","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Reason","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"iOS"}],"type":"strong"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fullScreenCover"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A subscription paywall is a primary moment, not an interrupt. ","type":"text"},{"code":"fullScreenCover","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" keeps the UI immersive, prevents accidental gesture-dismiss, and matches App Store conventions.","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"macOS"}]}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sheet"},{"type":"text","text":" with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"frame(minWidth: 400, minHeight: 600)"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Mac sheets do not expand to fill the parent window. Without an explicit minimum size the paywall would render too small to legibly show plan options. The 400×600 minimum is roughly the size RevenueCatUI’s templates assume.","type":"text"}]}]]]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The minimum frame is hard-coded; it is not exposed as a parameter. If your paywall layout needs more room on macOS, wrap the modified view in a parent that imposes a larger frame, or use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatUI.PaywallView"},{"type":"text","text":" directly inside a custom "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sheet"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier."}]},{"level":2,"text":"revenueCatCustomerCenter","type":"heading","anchor":"revenueCatCustomerCenter"},{"header":"row","type":"table","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Platform"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Presentation"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Reason"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"iOS"}]}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sheet"},{"type":"text","text":" with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatUI.CustomerCenterView"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"RevenueCatUI ships a customer center on iOS only. A non-fullscreen "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sheet"},{"type":"text","text":" is appropriate because customer-center actions are administrative, not part of a purchase flow."}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"macOS"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Opens "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"itms-apps:\/\/apps.apple.com\/account\/subscriptions"},{"type":"text","text":" and immediately fires "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onDismiss"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"RevenueCatUI does not ship a customer center on macOS, and the system has no equivalent in-app surface. The App Store subscription management page is what users expect on the Mac, so the sheet hands off to it and clears its own presentation state immediately.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The macOS branch clears the binding and fires "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onDismiss"},{"type":"text","text":" synchronously after "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSWorkspace.shared.open"},{"type":"text","text":" so "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallState.isCustomerCenterPresented"},{"type":"text","text":" does not get stuck "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":". The user returns from App Store to find the app’s UI in its idle state."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Why no platform-override hooks","anchor":"Why-no-platform-override-hooks","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Both modifiers are deliberately parameter-light: an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isPresented: Binding<Bool>"},{"type":"text","text":" and an optional "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onDismiss: () -> Void"},{"type":"text","text":". There is no "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"paywallStyle:"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"presentationKind:","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The reasoning: any consumer that needs to deviate from the chosen presentation already has the underlying RevenueCatUI types (","type":"text"},{"code":"PaywallView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"CustomerCenterView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") and SwiftUI’s full presentation surface (","type":"text"},{"code":"sheet","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"fullScreenCover","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"popover","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", custom containers). The bundled modifiers exist to handle the 95% case in one line — when the 5% case applies, drop down to RevenueCatUI directly.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This package does not try to be the complete paywall-UI library. It is the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"integration layer"}]},{"type":"text","text":" that makes the common case trivial."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"What-is-configurable","text":"What is configurable","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The configurable surface lives in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatUI"},{"type":"text","text":" and on the paywall plugin:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Paywall content, copy, and template"}]},{"text":" — configured in the RevenueCat dashboard. ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatUI.PaywallView"},{"text":" renders whichever offering and template the dashboard returns.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Customer-center labels, sections, and actions","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — configured in the RevenueCat dashboard. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatUI.CustomerCenterView"},{"type":"text","text":" renders whichever configuration the dashboard returns."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Presentation triggering"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — driven by the plugin via ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallState.isPresented"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isCustomerCenterPresented"},{"text":". Your code chooses ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"when","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" to set them via ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".request(reason:)"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".presentCustomerCenter"},{"text":" actions.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Dismiss behavior","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — your ","type":"text"},{"code":"onDismiss","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" closures dispatch the matching paywall actions. Replace them if you need analytics hooks or cleanup beyond the default flow.","type":"text"}]}]}]}]}],"sections":[],"kind":"article","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/platformbehavior"]}],"metadata":{"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article","title":"Platform Behavior","modules":[{"name":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/PlatformBehavior","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"text":"Why the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"revenueCatPaywall"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"revenueCatCustomerCenter"},{"text":" modifiers present differently on iOS and macOS, and what is hard-coded.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"references":{"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/EntitlementMapping":{"url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/entitlementmapping","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/EntitlementMapping","abstract":[{"text":"How RevenueCat’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"CustomerInfo.entitlements","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" translates to Swidux’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"EntitlementSnapshot","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","role":"article","type":"topic","title":"Entitlement Mapping"},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","abstract":[{"text":"RevenueCat adapter for Swidux’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"PaywallPlugin","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Implements ","type":"text"},{"code":"PaywallService","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" against ","type":"text"},{"code":"Purchases.shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ships a controllable mock for previews and tests, and pairs with ","type":"text"},{"code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for drop-in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallView"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CustomerCenterView"},{"type":"text","text":" presentation."}]},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/HowToPresentTheUI":{"title":"How to Present the UI","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/howtopresenttheui","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPresentTheUI","abstract":[{"text":"Attach the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"revenueCatPaywall"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"revenueCatCustomerCenter"},{"text":" view modifiers from ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI"},{"type":"text","text":" to a root view, driven by "},{"code":"PaywallState","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"topic"}}}